title: Export multiple files with the same file name under different directories to a zip file fails.
EB: The zip file fails to store multiple files with the same name under different directories. For example, if there are two files with the name 'foo.txt' in different projects, the zip file only includes one of them (e.g. 'foo.txt' in project 1). If you name the second 'foo.txt' as 'foo2.txt' in project 2, there are no problems.
